Modules.Tunnel Vision:
{{Main|Tunnel Vision}}
{{Quote|The recovery of two pieces of a lost dwarven relic has revealed the location of the third and final piece. Driven by prophecy the Dwarves of the Vast struggle against time and fate to restore the Hammer of Thanes, but time is short and a darkness is trying to corrupt the quest.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[James Traino]], [[Frank Timar]]
* '''Released:''' January 2001
''Part 5 of the "Destiny of Dwarves" series.''

Modules.Ineffable Tome:
{{Main|Ineffable Tome}}
{{Quote|Skilled adventurers are needed immediately at the Temple of Mystra. An ally of the temple has stolen a powerful evil artifact, and it must be protected as it is taken to a place where no evil force can reach it. Expect trouble, as the evil foes from which the artifact was taken will stop at nothing to get it back.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gregory A. Dreher]]
* '''Released:''' January 2001

Modules.Dragon's Rage:
{{Main|Dragon's Rage}}
{{Quote|You have heard that the famed sage Elminster resides in the small village known as Shadowdale. You head there to find the next clue in the Prophecy of the Dragon Sage. You would never have guessed that your foes have the same writings that you do, until you get there&hellip;}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jason Nichils]], [[Troy Daniels]]
* '''Released:''' January 2001
''Part 5 of the "Cycle of Dragons" series.''

Modules.Pirates of Yore:
{{Main|Pirates of Yore}}
{{Quote|A merchant ship goes missing and an age-old pirate is suspected of the crime. However the story of the pirate and his family is still a mystery. Can you find out what happened to the pirate and the mysteries of the past?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel Cooper]]
* '''Released:''' March 2001

Modules.Pilgrimage:
{{Main|Pilgrimage (adventure)}}
{{Quote|The curse of Carthoun has manifested in Procampur as the city is overrun by an army of undead. A pilgrimage has come offering to save the Shining Jewel of the Vast from this threat, but will they bring salvation or defeat in their wake?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Andrew Hauptman]]
* '''Released:''' March 2001
''Part 13 of the "Cracked Jewel Saga".''

Modules.A Squire's First Errand:
{{Main|A Squire's First Errand}}
{{Quote|The Dove Knighthood approaches you to provide assistance in a "diplomatic matter." The request is vague, but a knight is always willing to help out another, right? An adventure recommended for knights, squires, and/or servants of Ilmater or the Triad.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Lee Sharp]], [[Michelle Sharp]]
* '''Released:''' March 2001

Modules.When Chaos Reigns:
{{Main|When Chaos Reigns}}
{{Quote|Screams in the night might indicate someone who has had a nightmare. What about during the day? What do you do when you are having nightmares while you are still awake? If you live in Ravens Bluff, you look for bold adventurers to find out what is causing them. And you hope they hurry, before you loose your sanity forever.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Alan Bonnin]]
* '''Released:''' March 2001

Modules.Full Circle:
{{Main|Full Circle}}
{{Quote|The city has decided to make a pre-emptive strike against the Circle of Four, to end the threat of this group forever. Adventurers are being called by the score into the mayors office, you included. With the destruction caused in previous Circle member appearances in mind, you are sure that Charles O'Kane is worried about the safety of the populace.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[David Samuels]]
* '''Released:''' March 2001
''Part 5 of the "Elementally Speaking" series.''

Modules.The Good, the Undead, and the Ugly:
{{Main|The Good, the Undead, and the Ugly}}
{{Quote|Hanging around Ravens Bluff and getting paid for it is nice, but what is it the city wants you for now? Guarding strangers is one thing, but saving them from curses?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[David Santana]]
* '''Released:''' March 2001
''Part 3 of the "Flight of Arrows" series.''

Modules.The Gift of Song:
{{Main|The Gift of Song}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Catie Martolin]], [[Rhonda Hutcheson]]
* '''Released:''' April 2001

Modules.Halur a'Moradin:
{{Main|Halur a'Moradin}}
{{Quote|You are invited the to the celebration to end dwarven celebrations, but then the lights go out and when they come back on, someone is missing, something is missing, and the party is over.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Frank Timar]]
* '''Released:''' April 2001
''Part 6 of the "Destiny of Dwarves" series.''

Modules.Swan Song:
{{Main|Swan Song}}
{{Quote|Cancelled concerts, quiet taverns, and postponed poetry readings&mdash;where have all the bards gone?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[C.E. Caldwell]]
* '''Released:''' April 2001

Modules.Wild Ride:
{{Main|Wild Ride (adventure)}}
{{Quote|You awake one morning with a strange mark of a silver unicorn horn on your forehead. All you remember from last night are dreams of unicorns dancing in a forest clearing. Mielikki calls, so bring characters who would be summoned by a nature deity. Fire-using characters are not welcome.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Christopher Jensen]]
* '''Released:''' May 2001
''Part 1 of the "Forest of Lethyr" series.''

Modules.Art Imitates Life:
{{Main|Art Imitates Life}}
{{Quote|Mystery abounds at a local art gallery as adventurers investigate a series of strange disappearances and odd occurrences. What happens when "Art Imitates Life" and then tries to choke the life from the investigators? Adventurers will have different views of "performance" art, "oil on canvas" and "life-like" sculptures after this adventure.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Todd Landrum]], [[Lance Thomas]], [[Richard Cain]]
* '''Released:''' May 2001

Modules.Broken Glass:
{{Main|Broken Glass}}
{{Quote|Someone has been burglarizing a shop belonging to the Thayan Magic Trading Company. The word on the street is that the previous owner had hidden a powerful item somewhere on the premises. Now the item might be used to destroy another.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Joseph Russell]]
* '''Released:''' May 2001

Modules.Family Matters:
{{Main|Family Matters}}
{{Quote|One of Ravens Bluff's most revered and a respected noble family is suspected of illegal magic trafficking and embezzlement. Has Lady Lauren DeVillars duped the whole town, or is this a plot against her by a rival?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Rebecca Ward]], [[Bill Ward]]
* '''Released:''' May 2001

Modules.Unmasked:
{{Main|Unmasked}}
{{Quote|Something is afoul on a noble's country estate, and you have been tasked to investigate the matter.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Mark Grotewold]], [[Chris Teegarden]]
* '''Released:''' May 2001

Modules.Family Ties:
{{Main|Family Ties}}
{{Quote|A local adventuring group uncovered evidence that a noble was framing Lady Lauren as a traitor and blackmarketeer. Now, justice must be served. That noble must be brought in to the City Watch and must stand trial.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Rebecca Ward]], [[Bill Ward]]
* '''Released:''' May 2001
''Sequel to ''[[Family Matters]]''''

Modules.The Case of the Missing Chef:
{{Main|The Case of the Missing Chef}}
{{Quote|An elderly Halfling hires you to find her missing son. Last she heard, he was working as a chef for a wizard living near Crow's End. The pay is not much, but how could you turn her down?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Harold Johnson]]
* '''Released:''' June 2001

Modules.Too Much of Me Is Magic:
{{Main|Too Much of Me Is Magic}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jean Rabe]]
* '''Released:''' June 2001

Modules.For Love Lost:
{{Main|For Love Lost}}
{{Quote|On a lonely trail outside of Ravens Bluff, a beautiful maiden needs your aid. Can you discover what happened to her intended who left to seek his fortune three years ago but never returned?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gary Labrecque]]
* '''Released:''' July 2001

Modules.Luck, Law, and Life:
{{Main|Luck, Law, and Life}}
{{Quote|Sirrus Melandor's body, and the amulet that stores his soul, are both within reach. Adventurers are needed quickly to bring this legend of the city back to life.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gail Reese]]
* '''Released:''' July 2001
''Part 3 of the "Luck of Tyr" series.''

Modules.Raison d'Être:
{{Main|Raison d'Être}}
{{Quote|So, you want to become an adventurer? Well what have you gotten yourself into now? Finding a lost child wasn't exactly what you had in mind, was it?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Stephanie Zuiderweg]]
* '''Released:''' July 2001

Modules.Hawk's Pride:
{{Main|Hawk's Pride}}
{{Quote|While investigating the robbery of a valuable bird stolen from the shop of an eccentric elven merchant, you stumble into an even greater mystery: a series of recent deaths within the ranks of the Knights of the Hawk have the knights in disarray and desperately looking for the culprit before word spreads throughout the city. Will your investigation into the robbery of a bird lead you to uncover darker secrets?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel Perez]]
* '''Released:''' August 2001

Modules.Forever Hold Your Peace:
{{Main|Forever Hold Your Peace}}
{{Quote|A well-deserved day of rest promises to provide an opportunity for relaxation and catching up with friends&hellip; until it is interrupted by an urgent summons from a distraught merchant.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Catie Martolin]]
* '''Released:''' August 2001

Modules.A Tale of Two Towers:
{{Main|A Tale of Two Towers}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Bill Kerney]]
* '''Released:''' August 2001

Modules.Death Rides Brown Wings:
{{Main|Death Rides Brown Wings}}
{{Quote|"Death rides brown wings from the north" the astrologers warn. Now there has been a rash of strange illnesses in the City of Ravens.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Lee Sharp]], [[Michelle Sharp]]
* '''Released:''' November 2001

